      '## Cost Comparison',
      'In San Antonio, traditional stucco installation runs about $8 to $15 per square foot for a three-coat system, depending on wall preparation, finish complexity, and accessibility. EIFS typically runs $9 to $18 per square foot installed, slightly more on average because of the foam board, mesh, and specialized finish materials. EIFS often pays back the cost difference through energy savings — the foam board provides R-4 to R-12 of additional insulation depending on thickness, which meaningfully reduces cooling costs in San Antonio summers.',
      'Repair costs diverge sharply between the two systems. Traditional stucco crack and patch repair starts around $300 for small jobs and is rarely complicated. EIFS repair almost always involves more labor because the foam, mesh, and base coat all have to be rebuilt in proper sequence, and any moisture-damaged substrate behind the foam has to be replaced. A serious EIFS water-damage repair can run $5,000 to $20,000+ if a large section of wall has to be opened up.',
      '## Maintenance Requirements',
      'Traditional stucco maintenance is simple. Walk your home twice a year, fill any new cracks with appropriate flexible sealants, repaint or re-coat every 10 to 15 years, and address any staining or moisture issues promptly. The system is forgiving — most problems are visible from the outside, easy to diagnose, and straightforward to repair.',
