      '## How to Tell Which System You Have',
      'If you are buying a home or you have lived in your house for years and are not sure whether your stucco is traditional or EIFS, there are a few quick tests. Tap firmly on the wall with your knuckle. Traditional stucco sounds solid and feels hard. EIFS sounds slightly hollow and gives a tiny bit under firm pressure. Look at the trim details — EIFS often has thick foam reveals and aggressive ornamentation that would be impractical in cement stucco. Examine an inconspicuous spot for any damage that has exposed the underlying material; you will see either cement and metal lath (traditional) or foam board (EIFS).',
