      'Stucco requires more attention. In San Antonio, you should budget for sealant replacement every 3 to 5 years, crack repair as needed (typically every few years due to our soil movement and thermal cycling), and a re-coat or repaint every 15 to 25 years. Over 50 years, cumulative stucco maintenance might total $8,000 to $15,000 — meaningful, but still far less than the upfront cost gap between stucco and brick.',
      'When you add installation plus 50 years of maintenance, stucco still comes out $10,000 to $25,000 cheaper than brick for most San Antonio homes. Brick wins on per-year cost of ownership, but only if you plan to stay in the home long enough for the lower maintenance to compound.',
      '## Durability in the San Antonio Climate',
